oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The Edward Ward Carmack Memorial on the State Capitol Grounds in Nashville, Tennessee. The sculpted figure is bronze with a brown patina on a granite base.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Carmack was editor of the Tennessean newspaper, a U.S. senator, and a temperance leader. He was shot to death in 1908 by political rivals. Nancy Cox-McCormack completed this piece in 1924.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Monuments & memorials; Capitols; Columns; Newspaper editors; Legislators
